{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each mode maps to a specific "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Virtualization.framework"},{"type":"text","text":" network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device attachment type. The mode determines how the guest’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"network traffic is routed relative to the host and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"external network."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Choosing-a-Network-Mode","text":"Choosing a Network Mode","type":"heading","level":2},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mode","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Guest → Internet","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Host → Guest","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Entitlement","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"✓","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Via resolved IP","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"None","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"✓","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Own LAN IP","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.vm.networking"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"✗","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"✗","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"None","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For host-guest communication without full network access,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" mode and communicate via the VirtIO socket"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZVirtioSocketDeviceConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"), which is always"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attached regardless of network mode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Bridged mode requires the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.vm.networking"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"restricted entitlement, which must be requested from Apple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Developer Technical Support.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"anchor":"Why-There-Is-No-Host-Only-Mode","text":"Why There Is No Host-Only Mode","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework provides three network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attachment types: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZNATNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZBridgedNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":". None of these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implements host-only semantics directly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A host-only mode would require a user-space virtual network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"switch built on top of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handling raw Ethernet frames, DHCP, and packet routing — a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"substantial subsystem that would need its own lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"management and security hardening. Rather than ship a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"half-baked implementation or silently fall back to NAT"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which would give VMs unintended internet access), this enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only exposes modes that the Virtualization framework supports"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"natively."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need isolated host-guest communication, use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the VirtIO socket device. If you need full IP networking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between VMs, use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" on a dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host-only network interface."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The network configuration mode for a virtu